1)A commit is a saved checkpoint of your code with a message, and GitHub just stores those checkpoints online.
2)A branch is just a safe workspace to make changes without breaking the main project.
3)git add . stages all your changes so they’re ready to be included in the next commit.
4)git add "filename" “Stage this specific file so it will be included in the next commit.”
5)Pull Request? A pull request is a request to merge your changes from one branch into another branch (usually into main).


